# A two-tier brand architecture protects the core while capturing premium upside
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Core Brand (Protect)
  - Reframe as "accessible quality" — not cheap, not premium
  - Address private label threat with quality story + value messaging
  - Maintain distribution breadth in mass and value channels
  - Defend with promotions only on non-core SKUs

@col:
  ## Premium Sub-Brand (Invest and Grow)
  - Launch separate visual identity with premium cues
  - Distribution: specialty, natural, DTC, and select premium retailers only
  - Price at 60–80% premium to core — premium pricing is a quality signal
  - Build with community, not advertising: founder story, ingredient transparency

@notes: The sub-brand needs genuine separation from the core — same logo with different packaging is not a brand architecture. Consumers see through it instantly.

